Here's the TUnit lifecycle at each scope:

## 1. Before/After Every Test in a Class

```csharp
public class OrderTests
{
    [Before(Test)]
    public async Task ResetDatabase(TestContext context)
    {
        await InMemoryDb.ResetAsync();
    }

    [After(Test)]
    public async Task Cleanup(TestContext context)
    {
        // runs after each test
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task Order_IsValid() { /* ... */ }
}
```

## 2. Once Before First / After Last Test in a Class

```csharp
public class OrderTests
{
    [Before(Class)]
    public static async Task OpenFixture(ClassHookContext context)
    {
        // static — runs once before the first test in this class
    }

    [After(Class)]
    public static async Task DisposeFixture(ClassHookContext context)
    {
        // runs once after the last test in this class
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task Order_IsValid() { /* ... */ }
}
```

## 3. Once Per Assembly (before any / after all tests)

```csharp
public class GlobalSetup
{
    [Before(Assembly)]
    public static async Task StartWireMock(AssemblyHookContext context)
    {
        // runs once before any test in the assembly
    }

    [After(Assembly)]
    public static async Task StopWireMock(AssemblyHookContext context)
    {
        // runs once after all tests in the assembly finish
    }
}
```

## 4. Once Per Entire Test Session

```csharp
public class SessionSetup
{
    [Before(TestSession)]
    public static async Task ApplyMigrations(TestSessionContext context)
    {
        // very first thing that runs
    }

    [After(TestSession)]
    public static async Task TearDownDatabase(TestSessionContext context)
    {
        // very last thing that runs
    }
}
```

---

**Key points:**

| Scope | Attribute | Must be static? | Context type |
|-------|-----------|----------------|--------------|
| Test | `[Before(Test)]` / `[After(Test)]` | No | `TestContext` |
| Class | `[Before(Class)]` / `[After(Class)]` | **Yes** | `ClassHookContext` |
| Assembly | `[Before(Assembly)]` / `[After(Assembly)]` | **Yes** | `AssemblyHookContext` |
| Session | `[Before(TestSession)]` / `[After(TestSession)]` | **Yes** | `TestSessionContext` |

**Bonus:** Use `[BeforeEvery(Test)]` / `[AfterEvery(Test)]` (static, in any class) to hook *every* test globally — handy for cross-cutting concerns like logging. The `Class` and `Assembly` variants (`[BeforeEvery(Class)]`, etc.) also exist.

All hooks can be `async Task` and optionally accept a `CancellationToken` as a second parameter.
